of effect, I'll start with a plugin instead. The main reason is that doing it natively is kind of a pain.",[12,44,46],{"id":45},"dust","Dust",[17,48,49,50,53],{},"This is a really nice package. Under the hood it actually uses PIXI's ",[39,51,52],{},"ParticleContainer"," method — you can see it right near the top of the source:",[55,56,61],"pre",{"className":57,"code":58,"language":59,"meta":60,"style":60},"language-js shiki shiki-themes github-dark-high-contrast","if (renderingEngine.ParticleContainer) {\n  this.Container = renderingEngine.Container;\n  this.renderer = \"pixi\";\n}\n","js","",[39,62,63,76,92,109],{"__ignoreMap":60},[64,65,68,72],"span",{"class":66,"line":67},"line",1,[64,69,71],{"class":70},"sWyjQ","if",[64,73,75],{"class":74},"sMAXC"," (renderingEngine.ParticleContainer) {\n",[64,77,79,83,86,89],{"class":66,"line":78},2,[64,80,82],{"class":81},"sCcAr","  this",[64,84,85],{"class":74},".Container ",[64,87,88],{"class":70},"=",[64,90,91],{"class":74}," renderingEngine.Container;\n",[64,93,95,97,100,102,106],{"class":66,"line":94},3,[64,96,82],{"class":81},[64,98,99],{"class":74},".renderer ",[64,101,88],{"class":70},[64,103,105],{"class":104},"sTRMh"," \"pixi\"",[64,107,108],{"class":74},";\n",[64,110,112],{"class":66,"line":111},4,[64,113,114],{"class":74},"}\n",[17,116,117],{},"The thing is, Dust simplifies a ton of the steps for you, so building particle effects becomes much easier and more convenient.",[17,119,120],{},[121,122],"img",{"alt":123,"src":124},"Particle effect","https:\u002F\u002Fimages.israynotarray.com\u002FblogImg\u002FJavaScript\u002F1578625565569.gif",[17,126,127],{},"Here are the main parameters it uses:",[55,129,131],{"className":57,"code":130,"language":59,"meta":60,"style":60},"d.create(\n  250, \u002F\u002F x starting coordinate\n  250, \u002F\u002F y starting coordinate\n  () => new PIXI.Sprite( \u002F\u002F how each particle renders\n    PIXI.Texture.from('https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FUEZBrqp.png'),\n  ),\n  starPart